</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7C66756A777848FF4B55D0BC568FA2" box="[151,1122,1993,2017]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273824/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" targetBox="[201,1400,1544,1957]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A777848FF4B55D0BC568FA2" blockId="3.[151,1122,1993,2017]" box="[151,1122,1993,2017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A777848FF4B55D0B9768FA2" bold="true" box="[151,322,1993,2017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">FIGURES 8–9.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C034D7E6A777848FE9555D3B9DB8FA2" box="[329,495,1994,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolora" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A777848FE9555D3B9DB8FA2" box="[329,495,1994,2017]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Idmon bicolora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24457946A777848FE2955D3BA7C8FA2" box="[501,584,1994,2017]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(Scale = 10 mm) 8. Dorasal view, 9. Ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A70784FFF1A5281B8C78941" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Antennae dark brown, about as long as 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A70784FFD4F5281BAA988F1" box="[659,669,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A70784FFD745281BA8C88F1" box="[680,696,152,178]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
of forewing costa, club yellow ventrally; palpi second segment erect, densely covered with long greyish white scales ventrally, third segment long and slender, distinctly protruding.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A70784FFF1A5309BC5B89E1" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Wings upperside with ground color brown, unmarked, cilia pale yellow, without secondary sexual characters. Underside of forewing with ground color the same as that on upperside, scattered with yellow scales at apex and the end of cell. Underside hindwing yellow, costa and termen brown, veins yellow, with brown spots in spaces Cu 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A70784FFEF75381B90789E5" box="[299,307,408,422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
to Sc+R 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A70784FFE4A5381B9AA89E5" box="[406,414,408,422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1.0">1</number>
and the end of the cell, the area belowr vein Cu 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A70784FFC0C5381BBEC89E5" box="[976,984,408,422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
light yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A70784FFF1A53ABBD538AD7" blockId="4.[151,1437,152,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13382A786A70784FFE5F53ABBA38898F" box="[387,524,434,460]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1304,1328]" captionTargetBox="[266,1329,778,1277]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[238,1349,760,1278]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 14. Male genitalia of Idmon bicolora sp. nov. 10. ring, lateral view, 11. tegumen, dorsal view, 12. valva, inner view, 13. aedeagus, 14. juxta." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273825/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
Figs. 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A70784FFE1B53ABBA38898F" box="[455,524,434,460]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="12.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="10.0">10-14</number>
</figureCitation>
). Uncus long, about twice longer than tegumen, deeply and broadly bifid at half distal portion, two arms long and slim, running slightly outwardly; socius absentt; gnathos well developed, membranous and separated each ether at tip; saccus rather long; valva simple, broad, with the distal portion shallow bifid, forming the ampullar and the harpal processes, the ampulla with upper margin hardly swelled, the harpe with lower margin slightly convex, outer margin straight; two processes separated at apex; aedeagus with subzonal sheath subequal to suprazonal sheath, and bifid in distal portion; juxta U-shaped.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7C66756A70784FFF4B5701BA248D11" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273825/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" targetBox="[266,1329,778,1277]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A70784FFF4B5701BA248D11" blockId="4.[151,1436,1304,1362]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A70784FFF4B5701B96A8D73" bold="true" box="[151,350,1304,1328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">FIGURES 10–14.</emphasis>
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D7E6A70784FFDF85700BAFF8D73" box="[548,715,1305,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolora" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A70784FFDF85700BAFF8D73" box="[548,715,1305,1328]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Idmon bicolora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24457946A70784FFD0E5701BB128D6C" box="[722,806,1304,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
10. ring, lateral view, 11. tegumen, dorsal view, 12. valva, inner view, 13. aedeagus, 14. juxta.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A70784FFF4B57B7B8C08D8B" blockId="4.[151,1436,1454,1643]" box="[151,244,1454,1480]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Remark</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC36FD6A70784FFF1A57CFBA8D8E28" blockId="4.[151,1436,1454,1643]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C034D7E6A70784FFDD057CFBBDE8DB3" authority="Chou &amp; Huang, 1994" authorityName="Chou &amp; Huang" authorityYear="1994" box="[524,1002,1494,1520]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Idmon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fujianana">
<emphasis id="B977EAEF6A70784FFDD057CFBAFB8DAC" box="[524,719,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="61">Idmon fujianana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF924B0C6A70784FFD0257CFBBD58DB3" author="Chou" box="[734,993,1494,1520]" pageId="4" pageNumber="62" refString="Chou, I. (ed.) (1994) Monographia Rhopalocerorum Sinensium. Henan Scientific and Technological Publishing House, Zhengzhou, 854 pp." type="book" year="1994">
Chou &amp; Huang, 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A70784FFC7E57CFBBD58DB3" box="[930,993,1494,1520]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily separated from the latter by hindwing underside covered with yellow scales except for costa and termen brown; discocellular margined brown with broad yellow outwardly; the area blow vein Cu 
<number id="3DCB24DA6A70784FFC0A542FBBEA8E07" box="[982,990,1590,1604]" pageId="4" pageNumber="61" value="2.0">2</number>
pale yellow; valva with the ampallar and harpal processes widely separated at apex.
</paragraph>
